#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:4
msgid "Mask Modifier"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:6
msgid ""
"The Mask modifier allows vertices of an object to be hidden dynamically "
"based on vertex groups."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:10
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:36
msgid "Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:13
msgid ""
"The Mask modifier can hide parts of a mesh based on two different modes, "
"selectable from this drop-down list."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:25
#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:20
msgid "Vertex Group"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:23
msgid ""
"When the *Vertex Group* option is selected, all vertices belonging to the "
"chosen Vertex Group will be visible, and all vertices which do not belong to"
" that group will be hidden."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:36
#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:31
msgid "Armature"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:34
msgid ""
"When in Pose Mode, vertices belonging to the Vertex Group associated with "
"the active bone (same names) will be visible. Vertices not in that group "
"will be hidden."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:41
msgid "Inverse"
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:39
msgid ""
"Normally, vertices belonging to the selected Vertex Group (or group "
"associated with the active pose-bone) will be shown. The *Invert* toggle "
"allows you to reverse this behavior, instead showing all vertices which do "
"not belong to the Vertex Group, and hiding those that do."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:45
msgid ""
"The Mask modifier only takes into account whether a vertex is part of the "
"group or not, the weight is not taken into account."
msgstr ""

#: ..\..\manual\modifiers\generate\mask.rst:48
msgid ""
"Thus, a vertex with a weight of ``0.0`` will be treated the same as a vertex"
" with a weight of ``1.0``, because even though it has no weight it is still "
"a member of that group."
msgstr ""
